          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-01-24T21:43:59Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Vehicular Terrorism Prevention Act of 2017</strong></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Homeland Security (DHS) to: (1) examine actions DHS is undertaking to combat the threat of vehicular terrorism, and (2) report to Congress.</p> <p> The report shall outline examinations of:</p> <ul> <li> the current threat level for vehicular terrorism, </li> <li> actions DHS is undertaking to guard against vehicular terrorism, </li> <li> how the threat of vehicular terrorism may be mitigated, </li> <li> the extent to which DHS is doing outreach or training with private sector partners in response to such threat, and</li> <li> actions Congress can take to help DHS mitigate the threat.</li> </ul> <ul> </ul>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-11-06T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
